===Etymology===
{{wikipedia|yes and no}}
From {{etyl|ang}} {{term|gea|ġēa|lang=ang}}, in turn from {{etyl|gem}} *{{term||jā}}. Cognate with Dutch {{term|ja|lang=nl}}, German {{term|ja|lang=de}} and Swedish {{term|ja|lang=sv}}. Related to existing English terms {{term|yes|lang=en}} and {{term|yea|lang=en}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/jɛ/}}, {{IPAchar|/jɛə/}} or {{IPAchar|/jæ/}}
* {{audio|en-us-yeah.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{audio|en-us-yeah-interjection.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|ɛə}}

